https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/7h1BTbZ25gwzZYNHAmE1wDw5fC6.jpg On a fateful evening in a Seattle dive bar, Josh Kuntz and a group of social outcasts put on a faux wrestling show to a crowd of enthusiastic bartenders. With crude language and satirical monikers, the guys “beat” the pulp out of each other in a clumsy ballet, earning cheers from the crowd. That evening, the Seattle Semi-Pro Wrestlers were born. Bodyslam: Revenge of the Banana!
